                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d480">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-01-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 16, 1895</hi>
                        </date>. (Received Feb. 4.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 396.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that an irade for
                    the female college at Scutari has this day issued, as I am informed by a
                    messenger from the palace. The irade is recognition of the “good work done in
                    educating His Majesty’s Christian subjects,” and it exempts the college forever
                    from the payment of taxes. It places that institution on a firm basis, as the
                    grant is irrevocable by the Sovereign.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">A. W. Terrell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
